    • Method Detail

      • logReport

        public abstract void logReport(java.io.PrintWriter out)
        The report will write its contents to the given PrintWriter. It is up to each individual implementation to format the output accordingly, however there is no need for flush() to be called, and close() should not be called.
        Parameters:
        out - The PrintWriter the reports contents will be written to
